history.content:
New to the tech scene at Berkeley? Come explore some of the most exciting tech clubs on campus! You'll hear from ANova, Blueprint, Codeology, and Mobile Developers at Berkeley at this infosession!
The infosession will be on Wednesday, Janurary 26 on Zoom.
ZOOM LINK FOR EVENT: https://tinyurl.com/abcdoftech
LINK TO FACEBOOK EVENT: https://www.facebook.com/events/493430608798818
----------------------
ANOVA:
Berkeley ANova is a student organization dedicated to making access to computer science education and opportunities more equitable, available, and achievable for students of all backgrounds. Our outreach and mentorship efforts strive to introduce students of all backgrounds to computer science. Our members go on weekly visits to our partnered schools either to enrich an existing computer science class, or to teach a project-based afterschool program. Find out more here: https://www.berkeleyanova.org/join
BLUEPRINT:
Blueprint is a student organization at UC Berkeley that develops web/mobile apps for nonprofits pro-bono and promotes technology for social good. This semester, we're recruiting for developers, designers, and external leads of all skill levels. We're so excited to invite all of you to apply to help us support nonprofits and grow our social good community.
All of our infosessions will be **ONLINE**. We will be holding them every day from Sunday, 1/23 through Thursday, 1/27. Find more info here: https://go.calblueprint.org/infosession
CODEOLOGY:
Codeology offers a supportive environment for members to grow within the computer science community. Join our community and gain exposure to a large breadth of industry technologies by building projects and developing professional skills at workshops led by members, alumni, and industry leaders. We're a group of students who are passionate about computer science education and exploration - if any of this sounds like you, we'd be excited to have you in our club! Find out more here: https://codeology.carrd.co/
MDB:
MDB is a vibrant and collaborative community of developers seeking to drive change within and outside of Berkeley. Our community fosters a passion for innovative ideas, inventive solutions for our clients, and exceptional development at large. MDB is a defining part of our Berkeley experience and continues to impact the lives of our members through an inclusive and supportive family far beyond the walls of the university.
